snippet.textDisplay: The place you went to is good for Malaysian Chinese food. Understandably so as your friend is Malaysian Chinese. I would highly recommend that you go to Rasa in Greenwich Village. They specialize in Malay food - Assam Laksa, Rendang, Nasi Kerabu with Ikan Kampung (fried Mackerel) and Nasi Lemak. Give it a try. Most Malay - Malaysian in NYC will point you there
